                <fr:title text="Scheme">Scheme</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  A <fr:link href="/schm-V16H/" title="Locally distributed space" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-V16H/" display-uri="schm-V16H" type="local">locally distributed space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,\mathcal {O}_{X})]]></fr:tex> is a <html:em>scheme</html:em>, if for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex> there is an open neighbourhood <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(U,\mathcal {O}_{X}|_U)]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:link href="/schm-IFX1/" title="Affine scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-IFX1/" display-uri="schm-IFX1" type="local">affine scheme</fr:link>. The full subcategory of schemes will be denoted as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Sch}]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-269K/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-269K</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-269K/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Topology of a general scheme">Topology of a general scheme</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  It is well-known that if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link>, then as a topological space it is <fr:link href="/topl-FII1/" title="Sober spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-FII1/" display-uri="topl-FII1" type="local">sober</fr:link> and <html:em>locally compact</html:em>. However, it may fail to be <fr:link href="/topl-GW93/" title="Quasi-separated spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-GW93/" display-uri="topl-GW93" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link> or compact.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-8ES8/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-8ES8</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-8ES8/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Open subschemes and open immersion">Open subschemes and open immersion</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a scheme, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> an open subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(U,\mathcal {O}_{X}|_U)]]></fr:tex> is again a scheme. There is a canonical inclusion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \hookrightarrow  X]]></fr:tex>. Morphisms of this form are called <html:em>open immersion</html:em>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-IKN8/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-IKN8</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-IKN8/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Coproducts of schemes">Coproducts of schemes</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  The disjoint union <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \cong  \coprod _{i\in  I}X_i]]></fr:tex> of arbitrary schemes is again a scheme. The structural sheaf on an open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is given by
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{X}(U) \cong  \prod _{i\in  I}\mathcal {O}_{X_i}(U \cap  X_i). ]]></fr:tex>
  They are indeed the coproducts in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Sch}]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
