                <fr:display-uri>schm-80MC</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-80MC/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="A scheme is affine iff it is spectral">A scheme is affine iff it is spectral</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  A scheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is affine iff its underlying topological space is <fr:link href="/topl-VV9N/" title="Spectral spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-VV9N/" display-uri="topl-VV9N" type="local">spectral</fr:link>, i.e. iff it is <html:em>compact</html:em> and <fr:link href="/topl-GW93/" title="Quasi-separated spaces" uri="https://charloced.github.io/topl-GW93/" display-uri="topl-GW93" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>8</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a scheme whose underlying topological space is spectral. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> be the distributive lattice of compact open subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{U_i\}_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> be a finite family of affine open covers of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>. For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_i]]></fr:tex>, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_i]]></fr:tex> is affine, and affine schemes are determined by their underlying topological space (see <fr:link href="/schm-1I73/" title="Affine schemes are determined by topology" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-1I73/" display-uri="schm-1I73" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-1I73/" display-uri="schm-1I73" /></fr:link>), we must have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{U_i} \cong  D_i]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D_i]]></fr:tex> is the principle quotient of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex> corresponding to the compact open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_i]]></fr:tex>. This way, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{D}]]></fr:tex> agree on this open cover, which implies that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X} \cong  \mathcal {O}_{D}]]></fr:tex>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors />
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>6</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://charloced.github.io/schm-DF6J/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-DF6J</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-DF6J/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Finite schemes are affine">Finite schemes are affine</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  As a corollary of <fr:link href="/schm-80MC/" title="A scheme is affine iff it is spectral" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-80MC/" display-uri="schm-80MC" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-80MC/" display-uri="schm-80MC" /></fr:link>, if a scheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is finite, then it is affine, since finite sober spaces are all spectral.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
