          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  We say a poset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>image finite</html:em>, if for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>, the upset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\uparrow  x]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>finite</html:em>. We view <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> as a topological space via Alexandroff topology.
</html:p>
